<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 14 at 4:29PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of central Davidson
County through 500 PM EDT...
At 428 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Linwood, or near Lexington, moving northeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail and localized
flooding.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Lexington, Thomasville, Linwood, Arcadia, Welcome, High Rock Lake
Marina &amp; Campground and High Rock Lake.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
